<title>SOUTH AFRICA: SAFRICA DBSA IN 316MLN RAND MPUMALANGA DEVELOPMENT.</title>
<headline>SAFRICA DBSA IN 316MLN RAND MPUMALANGA DEVELOPMENT.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-08-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>South Africa's Development Bank of Southern Africa (DBSA) said on Friday it would commit a minimum of 316 million rand for infrastructure development to the Mpumalanga province, north of the country.</p>
<p>The bank said in a statement the focus of the financial support would be on rural infrastructure for agricultural purposes and electrification.</p>
<p>It would also be directed towards bulk water supply, electricity generation infrastructure and municipal infrastructure.</p>
<p>The allocation excluded the 200 million rand approved in principle for the Witbank to Maputo toll road in a co-financing arrangement with the private sector, DBSA said.</p>
